# FixOnce — AI Memory Layer

> FixOnce never blocks development. It only enhances it.

## Disable

If the user says "work without FixOnce" or "no fixonce" — stop calling all MCP tools for the rest of the session. Work as a normal AI assistant.

## Session Start

Try to initialize FixOnce:

**MCP Tool:** `user-fixonce` → `auto_init_session`
**Parameters:** `{"cwd": "<workspace_root_path>"}`

**If it works** — show the returned context and follow the rules below.
**If it fails** — proceed normally. No retries, no errors, no warnings.

---

## When Active

- **Respect decisions** — if init returned decisions, ask before contradicting them.
- **Update goal** — call `update_live_record("intent", ...)` before starting work.
- **Log insights** — call `update_live_record("lessons", ...)` when you learn something.
- **Log decisions** — call `log_decision(...)` for architectural choices.
- **Search first** — call `search_past_solutions(...)` before researching from scratch.

## Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `auto_init_session` | Start session |
| `update_live_record` | Save goal / lessons / architecture |
| `log_decision` | Record a decision |
| `log_avoid` | Record an anti-pattern |
| `search_past_solutions` | Search memory |
| `get_live_record` | Read memory |
